    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to Hindu temple building complexes comprised of one main temple surrounded by four subsidiary shrines, the term meaning "five-shrined." five-shrined; five-fold; five shrines in quincunx formation; shrine complex with four sub-shrines at the four corners</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
